org.jivesoftware.smack.packet

Interface PlainStreamElement

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Element, TopLevelStreamElement
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ClientStateIndication.Active, ClientStateIndication.Inactive, Compress, Compressed, FullStreamElement, SaslStreamElements.AuthMechanism, SaslStreamElements.Challenge, SaslStreamElements.Response, SaslStreamElements.SASLFailure, SaslStreamElements.Success, StartTls, StreamError, StreamManagement.AckAnswer, StreamManagement.AckRequest, StreamManagement.Enable, StreamManagement.Enabled, StreamManagement.Failed, StreamManagement.Resume, StreamManagement.Resumed, StreamOpen

    public interface PlainStreamElement
extends TopLevelStreamElement
    Plain stream elements, ie. everything that is not a stanza as defined RFC 6120 8. Stanzas are Message, Presence and IQ. Everything else should sublcass this class instead of Stanza.

    It is important to cleanly distinguish between stanzas and non-stanzas. For example plain stream elements don't count into the stanza count of XEP-198 Stream Management.
